## Cohesion Audit: Kurt-Russell.md

### Central Thesis
Kurt Russell is a Type 9 organized around refusing to be claimed: he keeps his name off everything he builds and locates his worth off the resume, so the "laid-back" surface is actually the most deliberate thing about him.

### Thread Map

| Section | What it contributes | Links to thesis via |
|---|---|---|
| Intro (wine/GoGi) | The strange hook: famous since 11, name off his own bottle | Establishes "keeps his name off" |
| §1 Type 9 diagnosis | Names the engine: self-forgetting + 8-wing sovereignty | Defines "refuses to be claimed" |
| §2 Never worked / batting cage | Origin: Bing split love (baseball) from job (acting) | Explains *why* worth lives off the resume |
| §3 Disney kid → Snake Plissken | The merge pattern (Carpenter) + Tombstone exception | "Hands over the wheel," refuses the credit |
| §4 Did he waste his talent? | Critic pressure + empathy turn | Worth not on a resume, restated as choice |
| §5 Goldie / never married | The merge in love + the family he raised | Refuses ownership in both directions |
| §6 Feelings he doesn't show | The cost: buried anger, body-center muffling | The lid on the serenity |
| Rabbit hole | Wing/subtype/arrows/counter-case | Deep layer, opt-in |
| §7 Kurt & Wyatt / Monarch | Three-generation watch-from-the-stands payoff | Batting-cage spine pays off |
| §8 Name off the label | Closing: nothing could put its name on him | Lands the opening mystery |

Read top to bottom, that outline holds as one argument. The batting cage (§2) → watch-from-the-stands (§7) spine and the wine-label bookend (intro → §8) are doing real structural work, and the Tombstone beat in §3 is correctly placed as the exception that sharpens rather than breaks the thesis.

### Scores

