| Promise-Delivery Match | 9/10 | 0 |
| Reader Mental Model | 9/10 | 0 |
| Section Transitions | 8/10 | 2 soft |
| Internal Paragraph Flow | 9/10 | 0 |

**Overall Cohesion Score: 9/10** — reads as one unified piece; every section earns its place.

### The only two candidates worth touching

Both are *soft*, not broken. The H2 headings carry most of the bridging load, so the piece never actually loses the reader.

1. **§1 → §2 (Adequate).** §1 ends on the 8-wing and sovereignty ("let nothing own you"). §2 hard-cuts to "There was no pool in the backyard... There was a batting cage." The heading sets up the origin story, so it works as a punchy cut, but there's no concept carried across the seam. A one-clause bridge tying "where did this refusal come from" to the childhood would tighten it. (Also defensible to leave — hard-cut section openers are a deliberate device used elsewhere here.)

2. **§5 → §6 (Adequate).** §5 ends warm (dependable father, "stable ground other people grow on"). §6 opens analytically: "The Nine sits in the Enneagram's body center, the cluster organized around anger." The phrase "which surprises people who only see the calm" *does* reach back to the calm portrait, so the bridge half-exists. Could be made explicit by carrying the "serene/present" image into the anger turn.

### What's already strong (left untouched)
- Intro → §1, §2 → §3 (name-blurry/myth thread), §3 → §4, §4 → §5 ("something a resume cannot measure"), §6 → §7 (father "shattering" → father-son Monarch), §7 → §8 — all strong, keyword-carrying transitions.
- No orphaned threads: epigraph, wine label, Disney misspelling, batting cage, Tombstone, the "shattering" moment all get picked up or paid off.

### My recommendation
This file scores 9/10 on cohesion and has already had two structural passes. I did **not** apply edits, because at this level unrequested bridge sentences risk diluting punchy hard-cuts more than they help, and the two seams above are working through their headings.

The two soft transitions are the only places light bridges could add anything. Want me to:

